# TypeScript Standards

## Typing
- No `any`. Use `unknown` + type narrowing, or generate types from protos via `ts-proto`.
- Explicit return types on all public methods and service functions.
- Prefer `type` for object shapes, `interface` for contracts that may be extended.
- Domain models (`*.domain.model.ts`) and DB types (`*.db.ts`) are always separate — never reuse one as the other.

## Function size & SRP
- Max ~20 lines per function body. Extract named helpers if logic grows.
- One level of abstraction per function: orchestration functions call other functions, not inline logic.
- `max-params` is 4 (ESLint enforced). If more args needed, accept an options object with a typed interface.

## Error handling
```typescript
// ❌ swallow or rethrow raw
} catch (e) { throw e; }

// ✅ wrap with domain error, log once
} catch (e) {
  this.logger.error('Failed to …', { error: e });
  throw new MicroserviceException(Status.INTERNAL, 'Descriptive message');
}
```

## Misc
- `class-validator` decorators only on DTO classes, not on domain models.
- Avoid barrel re-exports inside feature folders; use them only in `src/index.ts` of each lib.
